title: For Sale:  JO.LO.AR. 9mm
postcontent: This is a very nice JO.LO.AR Spanish, 6-1/4"" tip-up Barrel, 9mm Largo, 9 rounds. Designed by firearms dealer and inventor JOse de LOpez ARnaiz (hence: JO.LO.AR.).  They were manufactured from 1928 t0 1931 and were designed for the cavalry with a cocking lever on the right side so that they could be cocked with one hand while riding.  They function like a normal pistol without the lever and a lot of people took the lever off because it was a nuisance if you weren't needing to cock with one hand.   One with a non-matching numbered lever with almost no finish sold for $550 (+shipping an FFL fees) on Gun Broker last month.

I purchased this rifle from Justin at BRO November 14th via Gunbroker. After sending him the money orders, the rifle was shipped UPS Ground to my FFL holder here in Carson City. The rifle was scanned at the UPS hub November 20th and put on the truck for delivery. The UPS driver claims he delivered the rifle that afternoon and left it on the FFLs front porch. I'm attaching pictures of the rifle with hopes that this might help the Carson City sheriff's department and the ATF locate it. If you know anything about this matter, please email me as soon as possible.

title: For Sale:  Read ATF regulation before selling reloads
postcontent:
Is a person who reloads ammunition required to be licensed as a manufacturer?

Yes, if the person engages in the business of selling or distributing reloads for the purpose of livelihood and profit. No, if the person reloads only for personal use.

[18 U.S.C. 922(a) (i) and 923(a), 27 CFR 478.41]

It is also a liability issue.  You sell a reload someone gets hurt shooting it, you're liable.

title: For Sale:  KEL-TEC KSG OD GREEN 12GA 14+1rds NIB NO CC FEES
postcontent:
KEL-TEC KSG OD GREEN 12GA 14+1rds NIB NO CC FEES
Item Description

This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard. The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil. The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

SPECIFICATIONS:
Mfg Item Num: KSG/GREEN
Manufacturer: Kel Tec
Category: TACTICAL SHOTGUNS
Action :Pump
Gauge :12 Gauge
Barrel Length :18.5"
Capacity :14+1
Chamber :3"
OAL :26.1"
Weight :6.9 lbs
Receiver: OD GREEN w/ Picatinny Sight & Under Rail
Payment

I accept Credit Card Payments through Gunbroker Checkout. I do NOT charge a credit card processing fee. I also take money orders, cashiers checks, and personal checks. I will not ship until all funds have posted to my account.

For help using Gunbroker Checkout, you can click on "Tools for Buyers", then scroll down to "After the Auction" and click on "Checkout". It is an easy, safe and secure way of paying quickly with a credit card.

Shipping

After the auction has ended, it is your responsibility to provide me with a copy of the FFL I will ship the fierarm to. Please have your FFL put either your name, auction number, or both on their FFL. My fax number and email are can be found under my contact information. I am a licensed FFL, and can only ship firearms to other licensed FFL's.

I ship all of my long guns and ammo via FedEx Ground and all hand guns and most accessories via USPS. Please make sure your email address listed under your account info is correct. You will be email the tracking information from either FedEx or USPS(depending on the item) to that email address.

Shipping to Alaska and Hawaii will have to calculated, it unfortunately cost more to ship there. Continental US can see the shipping rates listed under "Shipping".

I ship within 3 business days after the payment has posted to my account.

Other

I work Monday-Friday 9:00 am to 5:00 pm CST. I am usually very prompt, in return of emails and phone calls during this time. I realize my auctions will end during the weekend and on Holidays. I will try to answer questions, and return emails during those times, but there may be a delay. If I am unable to, I will respond the next business day. Please do not call during the weekend or holidays unless it is an emergency.

I also, on rare occasion, sale an item in my shop before I am able to take the listing off Gunbroker. If this happens I will let you know promptly.

Most of my listings are "stock" pictures. I do this mainly to save time, but also to protect the serial number of the guns being sold.
